  <main>
    <h2>📐 Triangle Trig — What is <code>tan A</code>?</h2>

    <div class="img">
      <img src="../assets/triangle-5307879f.png" alt="Triangle diagram showing ABC with AB = 54 and angle B = 30°" width="300">
    </div>

    <p><strong>Right triangle <code>ABC</code> is shown. What is the value of <code>tan A</code>?</strong></p>

    <div class="choice">A. <code>\(\frac{\sqrt{3}}{54}\)</code></div>
    <div class="choice">B. <code>\(\frac{1}{\sqrt{3}}\)</code></div>
    <div class="choice correct">C. <code>\(\sqrt{3}\)</code></div>
    <div class="choice">D. <code>27\(\sqrt{3}\)</code></div>

    <h2>✅ Step-by-Step Solution</h2>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 1: Analyze the Triangle</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>Right triangle <code>ABC</code> has a right angle at <code>C</code> and an angle of <code>30°</code> at <code>B</code>.</li>
        <li>This means angle <code>A</code> is <code>60°</code> because the sum of angles in a triangle is <code>180°</code>.</li>
        <li>We are given the hypotenuse <code>AB = 54</code>.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 2: Use 30-60-90 Triangle Ratios</strong>
      <ul>
        <li>In a 30°-60°-90° triangle, side ratios are:
          <ul>
            <li>Opposite 30°: <code>x</code></li>
            <li>Opposite 60°: <code>x√3</code></li>
            <li>Hypotenuse: <code>2x</code></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Given <code>2x = 54</code>, we solve to get <code>x = 27</code>.</li>
        <li>This gives:
          <ul>
            <li><code>BC = 27</code> (opposite angle B = 30°)</li>
            <li><code>AC = 27√3</code> (opposite angle A = 60°)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>Step 3: Apply the Tangent Definition</strong>
      <ul>
        <li><code>tan(θ) = opposite / adjacent</code></li>
        <li>For angle <code>A = 60°</code>:
          <ul>
            <li>Opposite = <code>BC = 27√3</code></li>
            <li>Adjacent = <code>AC = 27</code></li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>So, <code>tan A = (27√3) / 27 = √3</code></li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="step">
      <strong>✅ Final Answer: <span class="correct">Choice C. <code>√3</code></span></strong>
    </div>
